00:00:26.670 --> 00:00:28.130
Good morning, everybody.

00:00:28.130 --> 00:00:30.300
Let's get started.

00:00:30.300 --> 00:00:33.060
Let me just begin by asking
if there are any questions,

00:00:33.060 --> 00:00:36.960
either about logistical issues
or about physics issues?

00:00:42.180 --> 00:00:42.860
OK.

00:00:42.860 --> 00:00:45.650
Today we'll be
finishing our discussion

00:00:45.650 --> 00:00:48.090
of black-body
radiation by talking

00:00:48.090 --> 00:00:52.480
about the actual spectrum of
the cosmic microwave background

00:00:52.480 --> 00:00:54.480
that we find in our universe.

00:00:54.480 --> 00:00:59.520
And then move on to talk about
the rather exciting discovery

00:00:59.520 --> 00:01:04.810
in 1998 of the fact that
our universe today appears

00:01:04.810 --> 00:01:09.480
to have a nonzero
cosmological constant.

00:01:09.480 --> 00:01:13.490
So I want to begin by reviewing
what we did last time.

00:01:13.490 --> 00:01:16.269
And one of the reasons
why I do this is I

00:01:16.269 --> 00:01:17.810
think it's a good
opportunity for you

00:01:17.810 --> 00:01:20.690
to ask questions that don't
occur to you the first time we

00:01:20.690 --> 00:01:21.190
go through.

00:01:21.190 --> 00:01:22.690
And that, from my
point of view, has

00:01:22.690 --> 00:01:23.950
been an extraordinary success.

00:01:23.950 --> 00:01:26.470
I think you've asked
great questions.

00:01:26.470 --> 00:01:29.010
So we'll see what
comes up today.

00:01:29.010 --> 00:01:33.440
We began the last
lecture by recalling,

00:01:33.440 --> 00:01:36.080
I think from the previous
lecture actually,

00:01:36.080 --> 00:01:39.810
the basic formulas for
black-body radiation, which

00:01:39.810 --> 00:01:42.280
is just the
radiation of massless

00:01:42.280 --> 00:01:45.020
particles at a
given temperature.

00:01:45.020 --> 00:01:48.800
And we have formulas for the
energy density, the pressure,

00:01:48.800 --> 00:01:52.370
the number density, and the
entropy density, all of which

00:01:52.370 --> 00:01:55.530
are given in terms of
two constants, little g

00:01:55.530 --> 00:01:59.580
and little g star, which
is the only place where

00:01:59.580 --> 00:02:04.230
the actual nature of
the matter comes in.

00:02:04.230 --> 00:02:08.150
G and g-star are both
equal to 2 for photons,

00:02:08.150 --> 00:02:10.310
but these formulas
allow us to talk

00:02:10.310 --> 00:02:13.590
about other kinds of
black-body radiation

00:02:13.590 --> 00:02:18.660
as well, black-body radiation
of other kinds of particles.

00:02:18.660 --> 00:02:21.280
As neutrinos are
also effectively

00:02:21.280 --> 00:02:23.690
massless, so they contribute.

00:02:23.690 --> 00:02:26.820
And in addition, e
plus e minus pairs,

00:02:26.820 --> 00:02:29.020
if the temperature
gets hot enough so

00:02:29.020 --> 00:02:31.880
that the mass of the
electrons becomes negligible

00:02:31.880 --> 00:02:35.770
compared to kt, also contribute
to the cosmic background

00:02:35.770 --> 00:02:36.820
radiation.

00:02:36.820 --> 00:02:38.504
And if we want the
higher temperatures,

00:02:38.504 --> 00:02:40.170
other particle will
start to contribute.

00:02:40.170 --> 00:02:42.750
And at the highest
temperatures all particles

00:02:42.750 --> 00:02:46.060
act like black-body radiation.

00:02:46.060 --> 00:02:50.430
The general formula
for g and g star

00:02:50.430 --> 00:02:55.220
is that there is a factor
out front that depends on

00:02:55.220 --> 00:02:58.210
whether the particle is
a boson or a fermion,

00:02:58.210 --> 00:03:01.860
a particle which does or does
not obey the Pauli exclusion

00:03:01.860 --> 00:03:02.870
principle.

00:03:02.870 --> 00:03:06.980
Fermions do not, bosons-- excuse
me, I said that backwards.

00:03:06.980 --> 00:03:09.670
Fermions obey the Pauli
exclusion principle,

00:03:09.670 --> 00:03:13.100
bosons do not.

00:03:13.100 --> 00:03:16.710
G and g star are
both 1 for bosons.

00:03:16.710 --> 00:03:20.170
But for fermions there's
a factor of 7/8 for g

00:03:20.170 --> 00:03:22.570
and 3/4 for g star.

00:03:22.570 --> 00:03:23.070
Yes?

00:03:23.070 --> 00:03:24.820
AUDIENCE: Would you
mind quickly restating

00:03:24.820 --> 00:03:27.270
why the positron-electron
pairs act

00:03:27.270 --> 00:03:29.657
like radiation above
that temperature?

00:03:29.657 --> 00:03:30.240
PROFESSOR: OK.

00:03:30.240 --> 00:03:32.690
The question is, why do
electron-positron pairs

00:03:32.690 --> 00:03:35.784
act like radiation at
these high temperatures?

00:03:35.784 --> 00:03:37.450
And the answer is
that radiation is just

00:03:37.450 --> 00:03:40.410
characterized by the fact that
the particles are effectively

00:03:40.410 --> 00:03:41.840
massless.

00:03:41.840 --> 00:03:44.110
And the effective
energy scale is

00:03:44.110 --> 00:03:48.450
kt, that's the average thermal
energy in a thermal mix.

00:03:48.450 --> 00:03:53.470
So as long as m e c squared
is small compared to kt,

00:03:53.470 --> 00:03:55.220
electrons and positrons
think that they're

00:03:55.220 --> 00:03:59.140
massless and act like
they're massless.

00:03:59.140 --> 00:04:01.680
And as I said, if you go to
higher temperatures still,

00:04:01.680 --> 00:04:03.755
all particles will act
like they're massless.

00:04:06.580 --> 00:04:10.160
Coming back to the
story of g and g star,

00:04:10.160 --> 00:04:12.430
we have the factor out
front which depends on

00:04:12.430 --> 00:04:14.350
whether they're
bosons or fermions.

00:04:14.350 --> 00:04:16.570
And then that just
multiplies the total number

00:04:16.570 --> 00:04:20.980
of particle types,
whereby a particle type--

00:04:20.980 --> 00:04:25.410
we made a complete specification
of what kind of a thing it is.

00:04:25.410 --> 00:04:28.300
And that includes specifying
what species of particle

00:04:28.300 --> 00:04:32.370
it is, whether it's a
particle or an anti-particle

00:04:32.370 --> 00:04:35.100
if that distinction
exists, and what the spin

00:04:35.100 --> 00:04:38.900
state is if the
particle has spin.

00:04:38.900 --> 00:04:43.890
So we can try this out
now on some examples.

00:04:43.890 --> 00:04:46.310
First example, will
be neutrinos which

00:04:46.310 --> 00:04:50.090
play a very important role
in the early universe,

00:04:50.090 --> 00:04:55.910
and even in the particle number
balance of today's universe.

00:04:55.910 --> 00:04:58.320
Neutrinos actually
have a small mass,

00:04:58.320 --> 00:05:02.090
as we talked about last time and
as I'll review again this time.

00:05:02.090 --> 00:05:05.630
But nonetheless, as far
as cosmology is concerned,

00:05:05.630 --> 00:05:08.490
they effectively act
like massless particles

00:05:08.490 --> 00:05:10.490
although the story
about why they

00:05:10.490 --> 00:05:13.775
act like massless particles
is a little complicated.

00:05:13.775 --> 00:05:15.400
It's more than just
saying that they're

00:05:15.400 --> 00:05:18.530
mass is small, for
reasons that we'll see.

00:05:18.530 --> 00:05:20.360
But anyway, I'm
nonetheless going

00:05:20.360 --> 00:05:24.410
to start by describing neutrinos
as if they were massless,

00:05:24.410 --> 00:05:27.520
as was believed to be the
case really until 15 years

00:05:27.520 --> 00:05:28.170
ago or so.

00:05:31.100 --> 00:05:33.390
The massless model
of the neutrino

00:05:33.390 --> 00:05:38.330
was a particle which
was always left-handed.

00:05:38.330 --> 00:05:39.890
And by left-handed
what I mean is

00:05:39.890 --> 00:05:42.680
that for neutrinos, if
you took the angular

00:05:42.680 --> 00:05:46.740
momentum of the neutrino in
the direction of the momentum,

00:05:46.740 --> 00:05:49.680
p hat there means dotted
with the unit vector

00:05:49.680 --> 00:05:52.360
in the direction of
the spatial momentum,

00:05:52.360 --> 00:05:56.650
you'd always get minus
1/2 in units of h bar.

00:05:56.650 --> 00:06:00.170
And conversely, all new
bars are right-handed which

00:06:00.170 --> 00:06:03.370
just means the same equation
holds with the opposite sign.

00:06:03.370 --> 00:06:06.370
So neutrinos always
have spins that oppose

00:06:06.370 --> 00:06:10.070
the direction of motion,
and anti-neutrinos always

00:06:10.070 --> 00:06:13.710
have spins aligned with
the direction of motion.

00:06:13.710 --> 00:06:16.140
Now, it's not obvious
but, if neutrinos

00:06:16.140 --> 00:06:22.350
were massless this would be a
Lorentz invariant statement.

00:06:22.350 --> 00:06:26.030
If neutrinos have a
mass, that statement

00:06:26.030 --> 00:06:28.720
is obviously not learn
Lorentz invariant.

00:06:28.720 --> 00:06:32.340
As you can see by imagining
a neutrino coming by,

00:06:32.340 --> 00:06:35.170
and you can get
into a rocket ship,

00:06:35.170 --> 00:06:38.770
chase it, and pass it, and
then see it going the other way

00:06:38.770 --> 00:06:41.700
out your window because
you're going faster than it.

00:06:41.700 --> 00:06:44.699
You would see the momentum
in the opposite direction

00:06:44.699 --> 00:06:46.240
from the way it
looked to begin with.

00:06:46.240 --> 00:06:48.960
But the spin would look like
it was the same direction as it

00:06:48.960 --> 00:06:51.740
did to begin with,
and therefore the spin

00:06:51.740 --> 00:06:54.041
would now be aligned
with the momentum

00:06:54.041 --> 00:06:55.415
instead of opposite
the momentum.

00:06:58.350 --> 00:07:00.310
So this could not
possibly hold universally

00:07:00.310 --> 00:07:02.840
if the neutrino has a mass.

00:07:02.840 --> 00:07:06.727
But for the time being our
neutrinos are massless.

00:07:06.727 --> 00:07:08.560
So we're going to take
this as a given fact.

00:07:08.560 --> 00:07:10.930
And it certainly is a fact
for all neutrinos that

00:07:10.930 --> 00:07:14.710
have ever been
actually measured.

00:07:14.710 --> 00:07:20.052
Given this model of the
neutrino, the g for neutrinos

00:07:20.052 --> 00:07:22.850
is 7/8 because they're fermions.

00:07:22.850 --> 00:07:24.830
Then there's a factor
of 3, because there

00:07:24.830 --> 00:07:28.670
are three different species
of neutrinos- electron

00:07:28.670 --> 00:07:33.610
neutrinos, muon
neutrinos, tau neutrinos.

00:07:33.610 --> 00:07:36.620
Neutrinos come in particles
or anti-particles which

00:07:36.620 --> 00:07:39.340
are distinct from
each other, we think.

00:07:39.340 --> 00:07:42.360
So there's a factor of 2
associated with the particle

00:07:42.360 --> 00:07:45.150
anti-particle duality.

00:07:45.150 --> 00:07:46.850
And there's only one spin state.

00:07:46.850 --> 00:07:51.530
The spin that's anti-aligned
with the momentum,

00:07:51.530 --> 00:07:53.520
or aligned for the
anti-neutrinos.

00:07:53.520 --> 00:07:55.510
But only one spin
state in either case.

00:07:55.510 --> 00:07:57.680
So just a factor of
1 from spin states,

00:07:57.680 --> 00:08:02.180
and multiplying that
through we get 21/4 for g,

00:08:02.180 --> 00:08:04.860
and 9/2 for g star.

00:08:04.860 --> 00:08:05.360
Yes?

00:08:05.360 --> 00:08:08.044
AUDIENCE: If we found out
that they were Majorana,

00:08:08.044 --> 00:08:09.710
that they were their
own anti-particles,

00:08:09.710 --> 00:08:13.970
would that change what we expect
the temperature [INAUDIBLE]

00:08:13.970 --> 00:08:14.930
to be?

00:08:14.930 --> 00:08:16.320
PROFESSOR: No, it would not.

00:08:16.320 --> 00:08:16.520
OK.

00:08:16.520 --> 00:08:17.740
The question was, if
we find that they're

00:08:17.740 --> 00:08:19.044
Majorana particles--
which I'm going

00:08:19.044 --> 00:08:20.419
to be talking
about in a minute--

00:08:20.419 --> 00:08:23.560
where the particles would be
their own anti-particles, which

00:08:23.560 --> 00:08:27.220
would mean that the right-handed
anti-neutrino would really just

00:08:27.220 --> 00:08:30.250
be the anti-particle of
the left-handed neutrino,

00:08:30.250 --> 00:08:33.490
it would not change these
final numbers at all.

00:08:33.490 --> 00:08:37.110
What it would do is, instead
of having the 2 for particle

00:08:37.110 --> 00:08:42.090
anti-particle, we would
have a 2 for spin states.

00:08:42.090 --> 00:08:45.285
So there would still be
two kinds of neutrinos,

00:08:45.285 --> 00:08:47.910
but instead of calling them the
neutrino and the anti-neutrino,

00:08:47.910 --> 00:08:50.490
the right words would
be right-handed neutrino

00:08:50.490 --> 00:08:51.545
and left-handed neutrino.

00:08:55.156 --> 00:08:57.749
But the product would
still be the same.

00:08:57.749 --> 00:09:02.050
AUDIENCE: Wait, they have
mass and they are Majorana?

00:09:02.050 --> 00:09:03.800
PROFESSOR: If they
have mass and Majorana,

00:09:03.800 --> 00:09:05.541
what I just said applies.

00:09:05.541 --> 00:09:07.040
The fact that they
have a mass would

00:09:07.040 --> 00:09:09.830
mean at the lowest possible
temperatures they would not

00:09:09.830 --> 00:09:11.820
act like black-body radiation.

00:09:11.820 --> 00:09:15.944
Kt would have to be bigger than
their mass times c squared.

00:09:15.944 --> 00:09:18.235
But that's only on the order
of electron volts at most.

00:09:22.060 --> 00:09:28.470
So I'll talk later about why
the true model neutrinos which

00:09:28.470 --> 00:09:30.260
have masses give the
same result as this.

00:09:34.190 --> 00:09:35.160
OK.

00:09:35.160 --> 00:09:37.280
Then we can also,
just as an exercise,

00:09:37.280 --> 00:09:38.365
calculate g and g star.

00:09:38.365 --> 00:09:39.490
It's more than an exercise.

00:09:39.490 --> 00:09:41.010
We like to know the results.

00:09:41.010 --> 00:09:44.510
We can calculate g and g star
for e plus e minus pairs, which

00:09:44.510 --> 00:09:46.800
is relevant for when
kt is large compared

00:09:46.800 --> 00:09:50.060
to the rest energy
of an electron.

00:09:50.060 --> 00:09:52.880
And again, they
are fermions so we

00:09:52.880 --> 00:09:56.240
get a factor of 7/8 appearing
in the expression for g,

00:09:56.240 --> 00:09:59.527
and 3/4 appearing in the
expression for g star.

00:09:59.527 --> 00:10:01.360
And then we just have
to multiply that times

00:10:01.360 --> 00:10:06.642
the total number of types
of electrons that exist.

00:10:06.642 --> 00:10:08.475
There's only one species
called an electron,

00:10:08.475 --> 00:10:11.280
so we only get a factor
of one in the species

00:10:11.280 --> 00:10:13.640
slot of the product.

00:10:13.640 --> 00:10:16.470
There are both electrons
and anti-electrons

00:10:16.470 --> 00:10:19.870
where the anti-electrons are
usually called positrons.

00:10:19.870 --> 00:10:22.620
So we get a factor of 2
in particle anti-particle.

00:10:22.620 --> 00:10:25.050
Two spin states because an
electron can be spin up or spin

00:10:25.050 --> 00:10:29.260
down, and that
gives us 7/2 and 3.

00:10:33.990 --> 00:10:38.200
Given that, we can go
ahead and calculate

00:10:38.200 --> 00:10:41.980
what the energy density
and radiation should

00:10:41.980 --> 00:10:44.200
be for the present
universe given

00:10:44.200 --> 00:10:46.980
the temperature of the
photons, the temperature

00:10:46.980 --> 00:10:50.360
of the cosmic
microwave background.

00:10:50.360 --> 00:10:53.900
And in doing that there's
an important catch which

00:10:53.900 --> 00:10:57.220
is something which is the
subject of a homework problem

00:10:57.220 --> 00:11:00.380
that you'll be doing
on problem set seven.

00:11:00.380 --> 00:11:03.460
When the electron-positron
pairs disappear

00:11:03.460 --> 00:11:06.680
from the thermal
equilibrium mix,

00:11:06.680 --> 00:11:10.400
if everything were still
in thermal contact,

00:11:10.400 --> 00:11:16.580
its heat would be shared between
the photons and the neutrinos

00:11:16.580 --> 00:11:19.770
in a way that would keep
a common temperature.

00:11:19.770 --> 00:11:25.220
But in fact, when the e plus
e minus pairs disappear,

00:11:25.220 --> 00:11:27.350
things are not in
thermal contact anymore.

00:11:27.350 --> 00:11:29.600
And in particular, the
neutrinos have decoupled.

00:11:29.600 --> 00:11:32.350
They're effectively not
interacting with anything

00:11:32.350 --> 00:11:33.640
anymore.

00:11:33.640 --> 00:11:36.320
So the neutrinos keep
their own entropy

00:11:36.320 --> 00:11:39.940
and do not absorb any entropy
coming from the e plus

00:11:39.940 --> 00:11:41.900
e minus pairs.

00:11:41.900 --> 00:11:46.890
So all the entropy of the
e plus e minus pairs gets

00:11:46.890 --> 00:11:50.190
transferred only to the photons.

00:11:50.190 --> 00:11:54.240
And that heats the photons
relative to the neutrinos

00:11:54.240 --> 00:11:57.260
in a calculable
amount, which you

00:11:57.260 --> 00:11:59.780
will calculate on
the homework problem.

00:11:59.780 --> 00:12:02.090
And the answer is that the
temperature of the neutrinos

00:12:02.090 --> 00:12:06.170
ends up being only
4/11 to the 1/3 power,

00:12:06.170 --> 00:12:08.907
times the temperature
of the photons.

00:12:08.907 --> 00:12:10.490
And that's important
for understanding

00:12:10.490 --> 00:12:12.870
what's been happening in the
universe since this time.

00:12:12.870 --> 00:12:17.699
That ratio is maintained
forever from that time onward.

00:12:17.699 --> 00:12:20.115
So if we want to write down
the formula for energy density

00:12:20.115 --> 00:12:24.460
and radiation today it
would have two terms.

00:12:24.460 --> 00:12:28.100
The 2 here is the g for the
photons, and this, times

00:12:28.100 --> 00:12:32.920
that expression is the
energy density in photons.

00:12:32.920 --> 00:12:36.790
The second term is the
energy density in neutrinos.

00:12:36.790 --> 00:12:39.370
And it has the
factor of 21/4 which

00:12:39.370 --> 00:12:42.210
was the g factor for neutrinos.

00:12:42.210 --> 00:12:44.470
But then there's also
a correction factor

00:12:44.470 --> 00:12:47.260
for the temperature, because
on the right hand side here

00:12:47.260 --> 00:12:49.200
I put t gamma to the fourth.

00:12:49.200 --> 00:12:52.420
So this factor corrects it
to make it into t neutrino

00:12:52.420 --> 00:12:54.470
to the fourth, which
is what we need there

00:12:54.470 --> 00:12:59.580
to give the right energy
density for the neutrinos today.

00:12:59.580 --> 00:13:02.850
And this is just that
ratio to the fourth power.

00:13:02.850 --> 00:13:04.810
And once you plug in
numbers there it's

00:13:04.810 --> 00:13:09.700
7.01 times 10 to the minus 14th
joules per meter cubed, which

00:13:09.700 --> 00:13:11.200
is, from the
beginning, what we said

00:13:11.200 --> 00:13:15.210
was the energy density in
radiation of the universe

00:13:15.210 --> 00:13:15.710
today.

00:13:21.581 --> 00:13:22.080
OK.

00:13:22.080 --> 00:13:26.120
Finally I'd like to come back
to this real story of neutrinos

00:13:26.120 --> 00:13:33.520
and their masses and why, even
though they have small masses,

00:13:33.520 --> 00:13:37.550
the answers that we gave for the
massless model of the neutrino

00:13:37.550 --> 00:13:41.280
are completely
accurate for cosmology.

00:13:41.280 --> 00:13:44.640
We've never actually measured
the mass of a neutrino.

00:13:44.640 --> 00:13:48.440
But what we have seen is
that neutrinos of one species

00:13:48.440 --> 00:13:53.650
can oscillate into neutrinos
of the other species.

00:13:53.650 --> 00:13:55.400
And it turns out,
theoretically, that that

00:13:55.400 --> 00:13:57.610
requires them to have a mass.

00:13:57.610 --> 00:14:00.100
And by seeing how
fast they oscillate

00:14:00.100 --> 00:14:02.320
you can actually
measure the difference

00:14:02.320 --> 00:14:06.254
in the mass squareds
between the two species.

00:14:06.254 --> 00:14:08.170
So it's still possible
actually, in principle,

00:14:08.170 --> 00:14:10.610
that one of the species
could have zero mass.

00:14:10.610 --> 00:14:12.380
But they can't
all have zero mass

00:14:12.380 --> 00:14:16.670
because we know the differences
in the squares of their masses.

00:14:16.670 --> 00:14:19.800
So in particular, delta
m squared 2 1 times c

00:14:19.800 --> 00:14:23.560
to the fourth, meaning the
mass expressed as an energy,

00:14:23.560 --> 00:14:28.420
is 7.5 times 10 to the
minus 5 eV squared.

00:14:28.420 --> 00:14:31.760
And larger values
obtained for 2 3,

00:14:31.760 --> 00:14:36.670
which is 2.3 times 10 to
the minus 3 eV squared.

00:14:36.670 --> 00:14:41.000
We're still talking
about fractions of an eV.

00:14:41.000 --> 00:14:44.670
The other of the three
possible combinations

00:14:44.670 --> 00:14:48.340
here are just not known yet.

00:14:48.340 --> 00:14:51.030
Now, if neutrinos have a mass,
that does actually change

00:14:51.030 --> 00:14:56.790
things rather dramatically
because of what we said about--

00:14:56.790 --> 00:14:59.760
the statement that the neutrinos
always align their spins with

00:14:59.760 --> 00:15:03.990
their motion just cannot be
true if neutrinos have a mass.

00:15:03.990 --> 00:15:06.840
And more generally,
for any particle

00:15:06.840 --> 00:15:10.950
with a mass of arbitrary
spin j, the statement

00:15:10.950 --> 00:15:14.780
is that, the component of j
along any particular axis--

00:15:14.780 --> 00:15:17.460
and we'll call it
the z-axis-- always

00:15:17.460 --> 00:15:20.590
takes on the possible
values in terms of h bar

00:15:20.590 --> 00:15:24.587
going from minus j up
to j with no emissions.

00:15:24.587 --> 00:15:26.170
It's different for
massless particles.

00:15:26.170 --> 00:15:29.400
For massless particles
every one of these elements

00:15:29.400 --> 00:15:32.550
on the right hand side is
independent and, by itself,

00:15:32.550 --> 00:15:36.990
a Lorentz invariant possibility.

00:15:36.990 --> 00:15:40.810
But, coming back to
neutrinos-- if the neutrinos

00:15:40.810 --> 00:15:45.880
have a mass, in addition to
the left-handed neutrinos there

00:15:45.880 --> 00:15:49.470
has to be a
right-handed partner.

00:15:49.470 --> 00:15:55.342
And the question then is,
what's the story behind that?

00:15:55.342 --> 00:15:57.050
And it turns out we
don't know the story.

00:15:57.050 --> 00:16:01.510
But we know two
possible stories.

00:16:01.510 --> 00:16:03.470
And one of the
possible stories is

00:16:03.470 --> 00:16:07.740
that could be what's
called a Dirac mass.

00:16:07.740 --> 00:16:10.300
And for Dirac mass
what it means is that,

00:16:10.300 --> 00:16:16.130
the right-handed neutrino is
simply a new type of particle

00:16:16.130 --> 00:16:18.470
which just happens to be a
particle that we've never

00:16:18.470 --> 00:16:20.970
seen, but a particle
which would have

00:16:20.970 --> 00:16:23.960
a perfectly real existence.

00:16:23.960 --> 00:16:27.920
It would however, to fit
into theory and observation,

00:16:27.920 --> 00:16:31.340
be an extremely weakly
interacting particle.

00:16:31.340 --> 00:16:33.170
The interactions of
the right-handed one

00:16:33.170 --> 00:16:35.510
do not have to be the
same as the interactions

00:16:35.510 --> 00:16:38.300
of the left-handed one.

00:16:38.300 --> 00:16:40.580
That is, the interactions
can depend explicitly

00:16:40.580 --> 00:16:43.016
on p hat dot j.

00:16:43.016 --> 00:16:45.270
So depending its
value, you could

00:16:45.270 --> 00:16:48.270
affect what the
interactions are, again,

00:16:48.270 --> 00:16:50.750
in a Lorentz invariant way.

00:16:50.750 --> 00:16:55.250
And in practice, the
right-handed neutrinos

00:16:55.250 --> 00:16:58.400
would indirect so
weakly that we would not

00:16:58.400 --> 00:17:00.410
expect to see them
in the laboratory.

00:17:00.410 --> 00:17:03.173
And we would not expect
even in the early universe

00:17:03.173 --> 00:17:04.589
that they would
have been produced

00:17:04.589 --> 00:17:06.640
in any significant number.

00:17:06.640 --> 00:17:08.710
So even though it would
be a particle that,

00:17:08.710 --> 00:17:12.829
in principle, exists, we
would not expect to see it.

00:17:12.829 --> 00:17:18.000
And we would not expected it
to affect the early universe.

00:17:18.000 --> 00:17:22.550
Alternatively-- and in some
ways a more subtle idea--

00:17:22.550 --> 00:17:24.805
is that the mass of
the neutrino could

00:17:24.805 --> 00:17:27.530
be what's called
a Majorana mass.

00:17:27.530 --> 00:17:30.400
Where Majorana, like Dirac,
is the name of a person--

00:17:30.400 --> 00:17:33.510
perhaps less well
known than Dirac,

00:17:33.510 --> 00:17:39.210
but made important contributions
in this context nonetheless.

00:17:39.210 --> 00:17:43.830
In this case, it can only
occur if lepton number is not

00:17:43.830 --> 00:17:45.650
conserved.

00:17:45.650 --> 00:17:47.780
And if lepton number
is not conserved then

00:17:47.780 --> 00:17:49.710
there are really
no quantum numbers

00:17:49.710 --> 00:17:51.210
that separate the
particle that we

00:17:51.210 --> 00:17:52.740
call a neutrino
from the particle

00:17:52.740 --> 00:17:56.000
that we call an anti-neutrino.

00:17:56.000 --> 00:17:59.190
And if that's the
case, the particle

00:17:59.190 --> 00:18:01.750
that we call the anti-neutrino
could, in fact, just

00:18:01.750 --> 00:18:06.740
be the right-handed
partner of the neutrino.

00:18:06.740 --> 00:18:09.190
So for the Majorana
mass case we don't

00:18:09.190 --> 00:18:12.850
need to introduce any new things
that we haven't already seen.

00:18:12.850 --> 00:18:15.570
We just have to rename
the thing that we've

00:18:15.570 --> 00:18:21.520
been calling the anti-neutrino
the neutrino with helicity

00:18:21.520 --> 00:18:27.132
plus 1 instead of minus 1-- it's
with j hat dot p with j dot p

00:18:27.132 --> 00:18:32.840
hat, equal to plus 1/2
instead of minus 1/2.

00:18:32.840 --> 00:18:34.590
So these would just
be the two spin states

00:18:34.590 --> 00:18:37.230
of the neutrino instead of the
neutrino and the anti-neutrino.

00:18:37.230 --> 00:18:38.271
And that's a possibility.

00:18:40.840 --> 00:18:43.670
And this would also change
nothing as far as the counting

00:18:43.670 --> 00:18:44.600
that we did.

00:18:44.600 --> 00:18:48.430
It would just change where
the factors go instead

00:18:48.430 --> 00:18:50.040
of having a factor
of 2 for particle

00:18:50.040 --> 00:18:53.670
anti-particle and
this type counting.

00:18:53.670 --> 00:18:56.322
We'd have a factor of 2
in the spin state factor,

00:18:56.322 --> 00:18:58.280
and a factor of 1 in the
particle anti-particle

00:18:58.280 --> 00:18:58.780
[INAUDIBLE].

00:18:58.780 --> 00:19:00.196
The particle and
the anti-particle

00:19:00.196 --> 00:19:01.250
would be the same thing.

00:19:03.580 --> 00:19:04.080
OK.

00:19:04.080 --> 00:19:05.140
Any questions about that?

00:19:10.490 --> 00:19:11.700
OK.

00:19:11.700 --> 00:19:15.260
Finally-- and I think this is
my last slide of the summary.

00:19:15.260 --> 00:19:17.510
At the end of the lecture
we just pointed out

00:19:17.510 --> 00:19:21.650
a number of tidbits
of information.

00:19:21.650 --> 00:19:24.300
We can calculate the temperature
of the early universe

00:19:24.300 --> 00:19:26.550
at any time from the
formulas that we already

00:19:26.550 --> 00:19:28.860
had on the slide.

00:19:28.860 --> 00:19:31.505
We know how to calculate the
energy density at any time.

00:19:31.505 --> 00:19:33.950
And by knowing about
black-body radiation

00:19:33.950 --> 00:19:35.970
we can convert that
into a temperature.

00:19:35.970 --> 00:19:39.690
And for an important
interval of time,

00:19:39.690 --> 00:19:44.000
which is when kt is small enough
so that you don't make muon

00:19:44.000 --> 00:19:47.850
anti-muon pairs, but
large enough so that

00:19:47.850 --> 00:19:52.470
electron-positron pairs
act like they are massless,

00:19:52.470 --> 00:19:59.310
and this very large range
kt is equal to 0.860 m e v,

00:19:59.310 --> 00:20:01.940
divided by the square root of
time where time is measured

00:20:01.940 --> 00:20:03.980
in seconds.

00:20:03.980 --> 00:20:09.296
So in particular, at 1
second kt is 0.86 m e

00:20:09.296 --> 00:20:14.410
v. And it does
apply at 1 second.

00:20:17.296 --> 00:20:20.070
Because 0.86 m e v
is in this range.

00:20:24.790 --> 00:20:26.570
We also then talked
about the implications

00:20:26.570 --> 00:20:29.340
of the conservation of entropy.

00:20:29.340 --> 00:20:32.670
If total entropy is
conserved, the entropy density

00:20:32.670 --> 00:20:37.620
has to just fall off like 1
over the cube of the volume.

00:20:37.620 --> 00:20:40.380
Total entropy is conserved
for almost all processes

00:20:40.380 --> 00:20:42.370
in the early universe.

00:20:42.370 --> 00:20:46.810
So the entropy falls
off like 1 over a cubed.

00:20:46.810 --> 00:20:48.560
And that means that,
as long as we're

00:20:48.560 --> 00:20:52.920
talking about a period of time
during which little g does not

00:20:52.920 --> 00:20:57.040
change-- and little g only
changes when particles freeze

00:20:57.040 --> 00:20:59.140
out, like when the
electron-positron pairs

00:20:59.140 --> 00:21:02.960
disappear-- but as long as
little g doesn't change,

00:21:02.960 --> 00:21:04.980
s [INAUDIBLE] 1 over
a cubed means simply

00:21:04.980 --> 00:21:08.670
that the temperature
falls like 1 over a.

00:21:08.670 --> 00:21:11.420
And when little g changes you
can even calculate corrections

00:21:11.420 --> 00:21:14.140
to this as, effectively
you're doing

00:21:14.140 --> 00:21:16.020
when you calculate
this relationship

00:21:16.020 --> 00:21:20.600
between the neutrino temperature
and the photon temperature.

00:21:20.600 --> 00:21:24.240
And finally, we talked
about the behavior

00:21:24.240 --> 00:21:30.220
of the atoms in the universe
as the universe cools.

00:21:30.220 --> 00:21:34.020
For temperatures above
about 4,000 degrees

00:21:34.020 --> 00:21:36.730
the universe, which
is mainly hydrogen,

00:21:36.730 --> 00:21:40.030
is mainly a hydrogen plasma.

00:21:40.030 --> 00:21:42.970
Isolated protons and electrons
zipping through space

00:21:42.970 --> 00:21:44.890
independently.

00:21:44.890 --> 00:21:48.340
At about 4,000 Kelvin-- and
this is a stat [? mac ?]

00:21:48.340 --> 00:21:54.830
calculation, which we're not
doing-- but using the answer.

00:21:54.830 --> 00:21:57.660
At about 4,000 Kelvin--
which is a number which

00:21:57.660 --> 00:21:59.950
depends on the density of
hydrogen in the universe,

00:21:59.950 --> 00:22:03.450
it's not a universal
property of hydrogen--

00:22:03.450 --> 00:22:05.860
but for the density of
hydrogen in the universe,

00:22:05.860 --> 00:22:09.800
at about 4,000 Kelvin
hydrogen recombines.

00:22:09.800 --> 00:22:11.105
It becomes neutral atoms.

00:22:14.090 --> 00:22:21.210
And slightly colder, at about
3,000, the degree of ionization

00:22:21.210 --> 00:22:23.800
becomes small enough
so that the photons

00:22:23.800 --> 00:22:25.800
become effectively free.

00:22:25.800 --> 00:22:27.630
The photons decouple.

00:22:27.630 --> 00:22:31.610
In between 4,000 and 3,000 the
hydrogen is mostly neutral,

00:22:31.610 --> 00:22:34.860
but they're still enough ionized
so that the photons are still

00:22:34.860 --> 00:22:37.420
interacting.

00:22:37.420 --> 00:22:39.170
So the most important
temperatures--

00:22:39.170 --> 00:22:41.940
the 3,000 Kelvin,
when the photons

00:22:41.940 --> 00:22:45.160
are released, when the
photons are no longer trapped

00:22:45.160 --> 00:22:48.640
with the matter of the universe.

00:22:48.640 --> 00:22:53.530
And last time we estimated the
time at which that happens.

00:22:53.530 --> 00:22:55.320
That should be a small t, sorry.

00:22:55.320 --> 00:22:59.510
The time of decoupling
is about 380,000 years.

00:22:59.510 --> 00:23:01.260
And that number is
actually very accurate,

00:23:01.260 --> 00:23:05.150
even though we didn't
calculate it very accurately.

00:23:05.150 --> 00:23:08.230
And that's the
end of my summary.

00:23:08.230 --> 00:23:10.420
Any questions about the summary?

00:23:16.560 --> 00:23:17.760
OK.

00:23:17.760 --> 00:23:22.400
In that case, let's
go on to talk first

00:23:22.400 --> 00:23:24.830
about the spectrum of the
cosmic background radiation.

00:23:27.280 --> 00:23:28.780
And then we'll move
on to talk about

00:23:28.780 --> 00:23:29.863
the cosmological constant.

00:23:46.270 --> 00:23:49.680
CMB is cosmic
microwave background.

00:23:49.680 --> 00:23:52.370
And that's a very, very standard
abbreviation these days.

00:23:55.410 --> 00:23:57.850
So when the cosmic microwave
background was first

00:23:57.850 --> 00:24:02.492
discovered by Penzias and
Wilson in 1965-- which,

00:24:02.492 --> 00:24:03.950
I might point out,
is going to have

00:24:03.950 --> 00:24:09.100
its 50th anniversary
in the coming year--

00:24:09.100 --> 00:24:11.840
they only measured
it at one frequency.

00:24:11.840 --> 00:24:16.800
It was a real tour de force to
measure it at the one frequency

00:24:16.800 --> 00:24:20.860
and to convince themselves that
the buzz that they were hearing

00:24:20.860 --> 00:24:23.500
in their detector was
not just some kind

00:24:23.500 --> 00:24:27.730
of random electrical noise,
but really was some signal

00:24:27.730 --> 00:24:30.090
coming from outer space.

00:24:30.090 --> 00:24:33.130
And the main clue that
it was some signal coming

00:24:33.130 --> 00:24:37.340
from outer space
was that they were

00:24:37.340 --> 00:24:41.702
able to compare it
with a cold load,

00:24:41.702 --> 00:24:47.720
a liquid helium-cooled
source, and find

00:24:47.720 --> 00:24:50.460
that that comparison worked
the way they expected.

00:24:50.460 --> 00:24:52.340
And the main reason
for believing

00:24:52.340 --> 00:24:54.599
it was cosmological
rather than local

00:24:54.599 --> 00:24:56.390
is that they got the
same reading no matter

00:24:56.390 --> 00:24:58.140
what direction they
pointed their antenna.

00:25:01.660 --> 00:25:06.770
This just took a lot of
radio technique skill

00:25:06.770 --> 00:25:08.520
to convince themselves
that it wasn't just

00:25:08.520 --> 00:25:12.674
some radio tube that was
malfunctioning or something.

00:25:12.674 --> 00:25:14.090
They even worried
that it may have

00:25:14.090 --> 00:25:18.510
been caused by pigeon
droppings in their antenna,

00:25:18.510 --> 00:25:21.600
I actually read about
in Weinberg's book.

00:25:21.600 --> 00:25:25.850
But they finally convinced
themselves that it was real.

00:25:25.850 --> 00:25:27.470
They were still not
convinced really

00:25:27.470 --> 00:25:30.510
that it was a sign
for the big bang

00:25:30.510 --> 00:25:34.470
and-- you may recall,
again, from reading Weinberg

00:25:34.470 --> 00:25:37.960
that there were two papers
published back-to-back.

00:25:37.960 --> 00:25:40.110
The experimental paper
by Penzias and Wilson,

00:25:40.110 --> 00:25:42.360
which really just
described the experiment,

00:25:42.360 --> 00:25:44.660
mentioning that a
possible explanation

00:25:44.660 --> 00:25:47.380
was in this other paper
by Dickie, Peebles, Roll,

00:25:47.380 --> 00:25:50.820
and Wilkinson which described
the theory that this

00:25:50.820 --> 00:25:55.010
was radiation that
originated with the big bang.

00:25:55.010 --> 00:25:58.720
But it's all based on one
point at one frequency.

00:25:58.720 --> 00:26:02.810
Shortly afterwards, I
guess within the same year,

00:26:02.810 --> 00:26:04.843
Roll and Wilkinson
were able to measure it

00:26:04.843 --> 00:26:07.160
at a slightly
different frequency.

00:26:07.160 --> 00:26:11.440
And when I wrote my
popular-level book

00:26:11.440 --> 00:26:18.300
I tabulated all of the data
that was known in 1975.

00:26:18.300 --> 00:26:22.350
And this mess is the graph.

00:26:22.350 --> 00:26:23.940
This shows sort
of the full range

00:26:23.940 --> 00:26:25.820
of interesting frequencies.

00:26:25.820 --> 00:26:30.180
The solid line here is the
expected theoretical curve

00:26:30.180 --> 00:26:31.850
corresponding to a
modern measurement

00:26:31.850 --> 00:26:37.412
of the temperature
2.726 degrees Kelvin.

00:26:37.412 --> 00:26:39.860
All of the interesting
historical points

00:26:39.860 --> 00:26:42.560
are in this tiny little
corner on the left, which

00:26:42.560 --> 00:26:45.610
is magnified above.

00:26:45.610 --> 00:26:48.230
The original Penzias
and Wilson point

00:26:48.230 --> 00:26:50.620
is way down here at
very low frequencies

00:26:50.620 --> 00:26:58.190
by the standards of radiation
at 2.726 degrees Kelvin.

00:26:58.190 --> 00:27:00.940
The Roll and Wilkinson
point is there.

00:27:00.940 --> 00:27:04.850
These blobs indicate error bars.

00:27:04.850 --> 00:27:08.240
The [? cyanogen ?] points
that you read about

00:27:08.240 --> 00:27:12.490
in Weinberg are shown
there and there.

00:27:12.490 --> 00:27:15.840
The first measurement that
showed that, it didn't only

00:27:15.840 --> 00:27:18.810
go up but started to go down
like black-body radiation

00:27:18.810 --> 00:27:25.110
should, was a balloon flight--
this 1971 balloon flight

00:27:25.110 --> 00:27:29.970
which produce that
blob and that bound.

00:27:29.970 --> 00:27:33.222
This was an experiment
by MIT's own Ray Weiss.

00:27:33.222 --> 00:27:35.670
And it was very
important in the history

00:27:35.670 --> 00:27:39.060
because it was the first
evidence that we weren't just

00:27:39.060 --> 00:27:41.070
seeing some straight
line, but we

00:27:41.070 --> 00:27:44.230
were seeing something which
did indeed rise and fall

00:27:44.230 --> 00:27:46.870
the way black-body
radiation should.

00:27:46.870 --> 00:27:52.070
A later balloon flight in
1974 produced error bars

00:27:52.070 --> 00:27:54.950
that are shown by
this gray area.

00:27:54.950 --> 00:27:56.990
Incredibly broad.

00:27:56.990 --> 00:27:59.840
So the bottom line
that this graph

00:27:59.840 --> 00:28:04.040
was intended by me to
illustrate is that, in 1975 you

00:28:04.040 --> 00:28:07.460
could believe that this was
black-body radiation if you so

00:28:07.460 --> 00:28:09.020
wished.

00:28:09.020 --> 00:28:12.140
But there was not
really a lot of evidence

00:28:12.140 --> 00:28:14.355
that it was
black-body radiation.

00:28:17.060 --> 00:28:21.680
The situation did not
get better quickly.

00:28:21.680 --> 00:28:25.950
The next significant
measurement came

00:28:25.950 --> 00:28:30.760
in 1987 which was a
rocket flight, which

00:28:30.760 --> 00:28:33.750
